===Etymology===
Latin [[passus]].  Its use as an auxiliary adverb comes from an accusative use (Latin [[nec]]...[[passum]]) in negative constructions – literally ‘not...a step’, i.e. ‘not at all’ – originally used with certain verbs of motion.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /pɑ/

===Noun===
